# Accessibility Review Checklist

## Purpose
Detailed accessibility review checklist for proactive code review. Reference this when reviewing code for WCAG compliance.

---

## Accessibility Review Checklist

### Semantic HTML

- [ ] **Semantic HTML** (not divs for buttons)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT
  <button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>

  // ❌ WRONG
  <div onClick={handleClick}>Submit</div>
  ```

---

### ARIA Labels

- [ ] **ARIA labels** (for icon buttons, complex UI)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT
  <button aria-label="Close dialog" onClick={onClose}>
    <XIcon />
  </button>

  // ✅ CORRECT - Described by
  <button aria-label="Book equipment" aria-describedby="booking-help">
    Book Now
  </button>
  <span id="booking-help" className="sr-only">
    Click to book the selected equipment
  </span>
  ```

---

### Form Labels

- [ ] **Form labels** (all inputs labeled)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT
  <label htmlFor="equipment">Equipment</label>
  <select id="equipment" name="equipment">...</select>

  // ✅ CORRECT - Inline label
  <label>
    Equipment
    <select name="equipment">...</select>
  </label>
  ```

---

### Keyboard Navigation

- [ ] **Keyboard navigation** (all interactive elements focusable)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT - Button is focusable by default
  <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>

  // ✅ CORRECT - Custom element needs tabIndex
  <div
    role="button"
    tabIndex={0}
    onKeyDown={(e) => {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
        handleClick();
      }
    }}
  >
    Custom button
  </div>
  ```

- [ ] **Logical tab order** (elements focusable in logical sequence)
- [ ] **Escape closes modals** (keyboard shortcut)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT
  useEffect(() => {
    const handleEscape = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
      if (e.key === 'Escape') {
        onClose();
      }
    };
    document.addEventListener('keydown', handleEscape);
    return () => document.removeEventListener('keydown', handleEscape);
  }, [onClose]);
  ```

---

### Focus Indicators

- [ ] **Focus indicators** (visible)
  ```css
  /* ✅ CORRECT */
  button:focus {
    outline: 2px solid blue;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* ✅ CORRECT - Custom focus ring */
  button:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--primary-color);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  ```

---

### Color Contrast

- [ ] **Color contrast** (WCAG AA: 4.5:1 for text)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT - Check with contrast checker
  <p className="text-gray-700">Text on white background</p>

  // ✅ CORRECT - High contrast for important text
  <p className="text-gray-900 font-bold">Important message</p>
  ```

  **Tools**: Use browser DevTools contrast checker or online tools

---

### Screen Reader Support

- [ ] **Screen reader support** (sr-only class for hidden but accessible text)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT - Hidden from visual display, available to screen readers
  <span className="sr-only">
    Loading equipment availability
  </span>
  ```

- [ ] **Live regions** (for dynamic content updates)
  ```tsx
  // ✅ CORRECT - Announce dynamic changes
  <div role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
    {loading ? 'Loading...' : `Found ${count} results`}
  </div>
  ```

