## Accessibility Standards

### WCAG AA Compliance
- ✅ 4.5:1 color contrast for normal text
- ✅ 3:1 color contrast for large text (18pt+)
- ✅ All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- ✅ All form inputs have labels
- ✅ Semantic HTML structure
- ✅ ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- ✅ Focus indicators visible

### Common Accessibility Issues
- ❌ Div buttons without keyboard support
- ❌ Missing form labels
- ❌ Low color contrast
- ❌ Missing ARIA labels on icon buttons
- ❌ Keyboard traps in modals
- ❌ Missing focus indicators

---

**Remember**: Accessibility is not optional. Always make UI accessible to all users.
